1
00:01:36,540 --> 00:01:40,606
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:01:40,630 --> 00:01:43,496
[Episode Three]

3
00:01:42,420 --> 00:01:44,236
I invited you here today

4
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:47,956
because I want to repair my image in your minds.

5
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:50,836
This is the batch that just came out.

6
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:53,300
Please enjoy.

7
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:56,476
That's wonderful!

8
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,796
Wait, wait, wait!

9
00:01:57,820 --> 00:02:00,220
It's not finished, it's not finished!

10
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:08,100
I can't write this for nothing.

11
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:11,460
It has to be commissioned.

12
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:13,716
Brother Zhong Fu.

13
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:16,356
Your writing is in a class of its own.

14
00:02:16,380 --> 00:02:18,396
It's hard to find a good writer.

15
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:20,956
As long as the gentleman is willing to write for us,

16
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:23,036
it's not a problem.

17
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:25,116
Okay, then I won't charge more.

18
00:02:25,140 --> 00:02:27,356
Two hundred silver dollars per print.

19
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:29,196
Don't worry, no problem!

20
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:29,916
Good!

21
00:02:29,940 --> 00:02:30,500
Don't!

22
00:02:30,524 --> 00:02:31,436
Don't rush!

23
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:32,596
We're not done yet.

24
00:02:32,620 --> 00:02:36,396
I'd like to write more than one.

25
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:38,820
One per month.

26
00:02:39,020 --> 00:02:41,156
What do you think?

27
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:42,756
One per month...

28
00:02:42,780 --> 00:02:43,796
Yes, monthly.

29
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:45,116
No, it's a bit strange, isn't it?

30
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:46,579
Aiyo...

31
00:02:46,603 --> 00:02:47,959
Aiyo...

32
00:02:47,983 --> 00:02:49,516
Aiyo... yoyoyo...

33
00:02:49,540 --> 00:02:50,876
This is rare.

34
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:52,396
One per month!

35
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:54,516
I've been with Zhongfu for so many years

36
00:02:54,540 --> 00:02:56,676
that I don't even have one of his calligraphies in my hand.

37
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:57,516
Naturally.

38
00:02:57,540 --> 00:02:59,916
What about you?

39
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:02,020
I'll take it if you won't.

40
00:03:03,660 --> 00:03:05,436
Brother Mengzou, Brother Zhong Fu.

41
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:07,876
You seem to have ulterior motives.

42
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:08,636
Right!

43
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:10,156
One per month, 200 per print.

44
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:11,070
We'll take it!

45
00:03:11,094 --> 00:03:11,756
Take it!

46
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:15,780
Good, Brother Menzou, write up the contract.

47
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:20,796
Brother Mengzou, what you just said,

48
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:22,869
Aiyo... aiyo...

49
00:03:22,893 --> 00:03:24,196
Aiyo... yoyoyo...

50
00:03:24,220 --> 00:03:26,500
It's so faked!

51
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:35,860
Brother.

52
00:03:35,585 --> 00:03:36,836
{\an8}[Chen Qiaonian, second son of Chen Duxiu]

53
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:38,076
Forget Henian,

54
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:39,796
but Zimei is a little girl,

55
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,020
how can she like this?

56
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:42,773
{\an8}[Chen Yannian, eldest son of Chen Duxiu]

57
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,876
I also want to buy her a doll.

58
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:44,316
But where is the money?

59
00:03:44,340 --> 00:03:46,180
Cut quickly!

60
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:48,036
It's a hot day!

61
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:49,716
What are you two doing in the house?

62
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:50,836
Is it hot?

63
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:52,476
Come and eat watermelon. Eat watermelon.

64
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,516
Come on, it's sweet. Come on, come on.

65
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:56,116
Thank you.

66
00:03:56,140 --> 00:03:57,820
Thank you Uncle Wang.

67
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:01,076
Let me tell you both.

68
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:02,156
In a moment, your father

69
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:04,300
will be talking to some important guests.

70
00:04:02,728 --> 00:04:04,516
{\an8}[Wang Mengzou, Manager of Yadong Library]

71
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:06,196
You have to think about the bigger picture.

72
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,156
Not like last time,

73
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:09,596
with frogs, snakes

74
00:04:09,620 --> 00:04:11,996
mites and other messy things.

75
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:14,900
Do that again, I won't allow you in.

76
00:04:17,380 --> 00:04:18,836
What's this?

77
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:21,100
It's for Zimei.

78
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:23,596
Did you hear what I just told you?

79
00:04:23,620 --> 00:04:25,556
Don't worry, I know what's important.

80
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:26,436
My problem with him

81
00:04:26,460 --> 00:04:27,996
was made clear that day.

82
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:29,796
He will not be embarrassed anymore.

83
00:04:29,820 --> 00:04:31,636
That's good!

84
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:33,156
Your father was a great man.

85
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:35,580
We can't let him get distracted.

86
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,820
Zhong Fu!

87
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:40,916
Brother Xing Yan, I'm glad you're back!

88
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:41,836
Missed you so much!

89
00:04:41,860 --> 00:04:42,516
Go, go, go!

90
00:04:42,540 --> 00:04:43,396
General Zou.

91
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:44,476
Brother Xing Yan, how are you?

92
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,620
Here I come.

93
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:51,116
That's really for Zimei?

94
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,836
And for Henian.

95
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:54,876
Right, right, right.

96
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,716
You two stay inside and don't go out!

97
00:04:56,740 --> 00:04:57,876
Eat your watermelon.

98
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,500
Alright.

99
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:02,076
Mr. Xing Yan!

100
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,956
Brother Mengzou!

101
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:06,276
Welcome, welcome, welcome!

102
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,716
Come on, come on, come on, have a seat.

103
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:08,956
Sit, sit, sit.

104
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:10,420
Have a seat.

105
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:12,636
Meeting Mr. Zhongshan and General Huang Xing

106
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:14,236
delayed a few more days on the road.

107
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:15,956
How's it going? What's the situation in Shanghai?

108
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:17,996
The anti-Yuan movement has taken root in people's hearts,

109
00:05:18,020 --> 00:05:19,156
it is unstoppable.

110
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:20,756
It's just that the Yuan forces' repressive tactics

111
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:22,396
are getting more and more brutal.

112
00:05:22,420 --> 00:05:24,316
Yes, there were many deaths everywhere.

113
00:05:24,340 --> 00:05:24,820
But I have no doubt

114
00:05:24,786 --> 00:05:26,420
{\an8}[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhong Fu, chief editor of "Youth Magazine"]

115
00:05:24,980 --> 00:05:26,756
that their actions will not be in vain.

116
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:28,060
By the way, Zhong Fu,

117
00:05:27,384 --> 00:05:29,822
{\an8}[Zhang Tuzhao, styled Xing Yan, organizer of "The Tiger" magazine]

118
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:30,260
you're always so efficient!

119
00:05:30,157 --> 00:05:31,224
{\an8}[Zou Yongcheng, styled Qi Zhi]

120
00:05:30,460 --> 00:05:32,196
So many comrades gathered at once.

121
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:33,876
It's not that I'm efficient,

122
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,196
it's that we've all been so desperate for so long

123
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:37,436
that we're going crazy.

124
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:39,716
It's a great opportunity to be active!

125
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:40,556
Right, right.

126
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:41,636
Let's meet then!

127
00:05:41,660 --> 00:05:43,316
Let me pass on Mr. Zhongshan's instructions

128
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:45,060
Alright.

129
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:48,796
The situation is now in our favour.

130
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:51,156
The world powers are at war in Europe

131
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:52,436
and can't be bothered with our China.

132
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:53,756
At home,

133
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:55,716
Yuan Shikai is trying to claim the throne

134
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:58,476
by increasing suppression of anti-Yuan activists.

135
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,876
But such a high-handed policy

136
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,236
has instead given us

137
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:02,756
a lot of public support.

138
00:06:02,780 --> 00:06:06,796
Thus Mr. Zhongshan and General Huang Xing

139
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:08,756
asked us to take active action

140
00:06:08,780 --> 00:06:09,980
to protect our country,

141
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:12,036
as soon as the time is right,

142
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:13,996
to overthrow Yuan Shikai's reactionary rule

143
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:16,356
to and create a new republic.

144
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:18,836
I, at the behest of Mr. Zhong Fu,

145
00:06:18,860 --> 00:06:20,516
ran the magazine in my hometown.

146
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,716
I organized a team

147
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:23,676
which has now grown to over two thousand members.

148
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,396
Whenever there is an incident in Yunnan,

149
00:06:25,420 --> 00:06:27,556
we in Hunan will be the first to respond

150
00:06:27,580 --> 00:06:29,436
and turn the world upside down.

151
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:31,540
Nice work!

152
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:33,876
Why do I get the impression

153
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:36,116
that Zhong Fu is in charge of the army?

154
00:06:36,140 --> 00:06:38,796
It's only been three days, you seem different than before.

155
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:40,236
I've heard you've got something big.

156
00:06:40,260 --> 00:06:41,276
Tell us about it.

157
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:45,836
I can't continue fighting and quarrelling forever.

158
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:48,716
I'm still doing my old job, writing.

159
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:52,196
For the past two months, I and Baisha have been staying at home

160
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:55,036
running a magazine called "Youth Magazine".

161
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:58,396
The goal was to promote a new culture,

162
00:06:58,420 --> 00:06:59,596
to create a new generation of young people

163
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,676
with the most advanced ideas

164
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:02,876
and theories in the world,

165
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:06,276
in order to replace the one that has ruled China for thousands of years:

166
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,756
the Three Principles of Confucianism.

167
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:09,516
Under the banner of science and democracy,

168
00:07:09,540 --> 00:07:11,076
a new generation of youth will be reinvented.

169
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:14,276
This is a sketch of the inaugural issue.

170
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:17,300
Gentlemen, share your thoughts.

171
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:19,516
Brother Zhong Fu,

172
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,876
why is there a foreigner on this cover?

173
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:22,756
Who is this?

174
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:24,196
Carnegie!

175
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:26,636
The steel king and philanthropist.

176
00:07:26,660 --> 00:07:27,876
He is Scottish.

177
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:30,676
At the age of eleven, he moved to America

178
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:33,796
and worked in a textile factory to make ends meet.

179
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,196
Firing boilers,

180
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,396
working as a courrier...

181
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:38,916
Then, through his own ingenuity and hard work,

182
00:07:38,940 --> 00:07:40,716
established his own company

183
00:07:40,740 --> 00:07:43,356
alongside Rockefeller and Morgan

184
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:46,220
creating a steel empire...

185
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:52,620
It became one of the three giants of the American economy.

186
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:55,996
The reason I put Carnegie

187
00:07:56,020 --> 00:07:58,316
as the cover of our inaugural issue

188
00:07:58,340 --> 00:08:00,116
is that we want to tell

189
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:02,876
the children of China who are still suffering

190
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:05,756
that the way of the world is left to the people of this world

191
00:08:05,780 --> 00:08:07,796
and where there is a will, there is a way.

192
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:11,876
Zhong Fu, you promote new cultures and new ideas.

193
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:13,756
I'm all for it.

194
00:08:13,780 --> 00:08:17,556
But if you reject Confucianism in its entirety,

195
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:18,756
I cannot accept.

196
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:21,076
Brother Xing Yan, not all of it.

197
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,036
Listen to me carefully

198
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:24,116
and in detail.

199
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:25,380
Let's go.

200
00:08:27,068 --> 00:08:30,991
{\an8}[Aurora University auditorium, Shanghai]

201
00:08:35,420 --> 00:08:39,996
Some people say that you, Chen Duxiu, started a magazine

202
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,596
to awaken the nation's political

203
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:44,956
and ethical consciousness.

204
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:48,076
So what is this awakening?

205
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,196
As everyone knows,

206
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:52,396
after Lin Zexu banned opium,

207
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:54,476
the British invaded China.

208
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,516
With their strong ships and powerful guns,

209
00:08:56,540 --> 00:08:58,076
we were defeated.

210
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,076
So some people suggested

211
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:03,036
that we should learn from the barbarians to control them.

212
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:04,756
This is the first awakening.

213
00:09:04,780 --> 00:09:06,396
Knowing that you are not as good as others

214
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:07,956
and the need to learn from them.

215
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:10,836
Later on, some people also further realized

216
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:12,716
that we are not only inferior in skills

217
00:09:12,740 --> 00:09:14,876
but also in country.

218
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:17,236
The foreigners had a more advanced system than we did,

219
00:09:17,260 --> 00:09:20,076
so they came up with the Hundred Days' Reform and the New Deal of the late Qing Dynasty.

220
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,356
Until the Xinhai Revolution overthrew the imperial system

221
00:09:22,380 --> 00:09:23,596
and established a republic.

222
00:09:23,620 --> 00:09:26,916
This is the second awakening.

223
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:29,316
But what about the establishment of the Republic?

224
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:31,636
The foreigners are still bullying us.

225
00:09:31,660 --> 00:09:33,876
The people still don't have enough to eat.

226
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:35,476
Here's why.

227
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:37,156
It's not just that we're not as good as others,

228
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:38,756
with a system not as good as theirs.

229
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:40,076
The most fundamental thing

230
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:43,636
is our ideological and moral philosophy.

231
00:09:43,660 --> 00:09:45,276
which is less advanced than others.

232
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:49,916
That's why I say that all enlightenment

233
00:09:49,940 --> 00:09:52,276
is ultimately the enlightenment of the mind

234
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,956
and the awareness of moral philosophy.

235
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:55,476
This is the final awakening.

236
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:58,836
In the end, it's all about human awareness.

237
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:02,556
This final awakening is to change our minds

238
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,956
to find the most advanced ideas in the world

239
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:06,756
to arm our people

240
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:08,476
to shape a new generation of youth

241
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:11,076
to create a new nation!

242
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:15,860
Yes! Yes! Yes!

243
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:24,596
For the new youth in contemporary China,

244
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:27,780
I think there should be six criteria.

245
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:32,356
First, one must be independent, not servile.

246
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:36,476
Second, one must be progressive, not conservative.

247
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:39,916
Third, one must be aggressive, not reclusive.

248
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:43,796
Fourth, one must be international, not isolated.

249
00:10:43,820 --> 00:10:47,876
Fifth, one must be practical, not illusory.

250
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:51,796
Sixth, one must be scientific, not imaginary.

251
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:52,956
The six criteria are,

252
00:10:52,980 --> 00:10:57,236
in a nutshell, that science and democracy

253
00:10:57,260 --> 00:10:59,236
should create a new generation of young people,

254
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:02,836
and the only way to do this is to use both science and democracy.

255
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:05,076
Science and democracy are the criteria

256
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:08,516
by which politics, law, ethics, academia,

257
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:10,556
social customs

258
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:12,076
and the daily lives of people

259
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:14,476
are judged.

260
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:17,236
Anything that is contrary to science and democracy,

261
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:19,956
even if it is the legacy of our ancestors,

262
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:21,916
the teachings of our sages

263
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:23,356
and the veneration of society

264
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:25,196
is not worth promoting.

265
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:29,140
Yes! Yes! Yes!

266
00:11:32,580 --> 00:11:36,076
Science and democracy are the sunrise,

267
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:37,116
but today

268
00:11:37,140 --> 00:11:40,676
the country is a mouldy, rotten

269
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,316
sore and bleeding

270
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:45,436
old house that is covered up tightly.

271
00:11:45,460 --> 00:11:47,956
How about letting the sun of science and democracy

272
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:49,436
shine on the house?

273
00:11:49,460 --> 00:11:51,996
In the past we used the simplest method,

274
00:11:52,020 --> 00:11:53,676
knocking down old houses.

275
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:55,996
But you knocked down the house!

276
00:11:56,020 --> 00:12:00,476
The mould, the sores, the glue are still hidden inside.

277
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:03,996
What grows is still rotten and dirty.

278
00:12:04,020 --> 00:12:06,196
So, China must be strong.

279
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:08,836
Not only do we need to knock down the house,

280
00:12:08,860 --> 00:12:10,356
but more importantly,

281
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:12,876
we need to dig out the roots of its decay

282
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:15,276
to bring about a profound intellectual revolution

283
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:17,516
using the ideas of science and democracy

284
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:19,436
to arm our youth.

285
00:12:19,460 --> 00:12:20,916
How to arm them?

286
00:12:20,940 --> 00:12:22,396
Everyone is looking for answers.

287
00:12:22,420 --> 00:12:23,476
My opinion is that

288
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,716
we should start with the daily life

289
00:12:26,740 --> 00:12:28,476
that is in our hearts and minds,

290
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,876
starting with our speech and writing.

291
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:33,556
Promoting the vernacular,

292
00:12:33,580 --> 00:12:35,596
to speak in words that everyone can understand

293
00:12:35,620 --> 00:12:37,916
and write words that everyone can read.

294
00:12:37,940 --> 00:12:39,836
We need to use the power of new literature

295
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:42,316
to enlighten the public mind.

296
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:45,961
Yes!

297
00:12:57,525 --> 00:12:59,522
Well spoken!

298
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:13,036
September 15, 1915

299
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:17,540
Chen Duxiu founds the "Youth Magazine" in Shanghai.

300
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:21,396
The New Culture movement for the enlightenment of modern Chinese thought

301
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:24,020
came into being.

302
00:13:27,461 --> 00:13:30,380
{\an8}[Waseda University domitory, Japan]

303
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:30,716
I say this Chen Duxiu

304
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:32,516
is really not a master of empty words.

305
00:13:32,540 --> 00:13:33,396
Just a few months after returning to China,

306
00:13:33,420 --> 00:13:35,676
he has done such an amazing thing.

307
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:37,556
It may be late autumn

308
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:39,036
but did you know?

309
00:13:39,060 --> 00:13:41,356
When I took from him this "Youth Magazine",

310
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:43,140
I smelt a whiff of spring.

311
00:13:41,684 --> 00:13:43,728
{\an8}[Li Dazhao, styled Shou Chang, student at Waseda University]

312
00:13:44,420 --> 00:13:48,260
Chen Duxiu is not a simple man.

313
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:50,538
It's finally happening

314
00:13:50,562 --> 00:13:52,095
{\an8}[Gao Yihan, student at Waseda University]

315
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:54,596
